                            <comment id="188749" author="adilger" created="Fri, 17 Mar 2017 10:37:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;If you upgrade both ZFS and Lustre, I believe it will transparently upgrade the quotas. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="188301" author="rmohr" created="Tue, 14 Mar 2017 19:18:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for the information.  When the fix comes, if we upgrade Lustre/ZFS, will it automatically fix the quotas or will we need to run some command to correct the current quota info?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="188286" author="adilger" created="Tue, 14 Mar 2017 17:31:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Rick, this is (unfortunately) a known issue.  There is new inode quota accounting for ZFS that is in the upcoming 0.7.0 release, along with a patch for Lustre in &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-2435&quot; title=&quot;inode accounting in osd-zfs is racy&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-2435&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-2435&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
